EMORY OF L. I. SHIGAEV


Andrew Field in his bibliography of my works says he has not been able to ascertain the exact date for “Pamyati L. I. Shigaeva,” written in the early 1930s in Berlin, and published probably in Poslednie Novosti. I am practically sure that I wrote it in the beginning of 1934. My wife and I were sharing with her cousin, Anna Feigin, the latter’s charming flat in a corner house (Number 22) of Nestorstrasse, Berlin, Grunewald (where Invitation to a Beheading and most o